caption: b'With temperatures dropping to downright chilly, we\xe2\x80\x99re embracing the warmth of home - daydreaming of future travels as marshmallows slowly sink into our hot cocoa. b'Sure. We all love an exotic island getaway, surrounded by nothing but sunkissed, white sandy beaches and palm trees. But as the seasons change and temperatures start to drop, we just want to cozy up in front of the fireplace in a far-off winter wonderland.\n\nSo for those of you dreaming of snow-tipped vistas and blissful quiet, hit the link in our bio and discover 6 snowy islands that are waiting to be explored again once the time is right.'

b'During a difficult year, including a global pandemic that is keeping us from experiencing travel the way we used to, it\xe2\x80\x99s time to remember that we don\xe2\x80\x99t need to travel far to rediscover some of the international cultures that unite the U.S. as a nation. #AmericaIsForEveryone'

b'#AmericaIsForEveryone

We\xe2\x80\x99re inviting Americans to reconnect with some of the cultures and places that unite the U.S. as a nation. We\xe2\x80\x99ve partnered with 10 properties across the country that celebrate some of the amazing cultures from around the world right in their own backyard.

From a traditional Dutch inn to converted lofts to a pagoda-inspired hotel, all 10 experiences open for limited bookings exclusively through Booking.com on Nov. 16. Click the link in our bio for full details.

We advise travelers to follow any travel advice updates from local government and health organizations, including state-to-state travel regulations.'

b'We went out onto the streets of London to put the travel knowledge of Londoners to the test. Their answers will definitely surprise you. Can you do better?'

b"Recently, we asked UK-based photographer @postcardsbyhannah to #ExploreNextDoor. Here\xe2\x80\x99s what she discovered:

\xe2\x80\x9cLooking back on my stay in the Cotswolds, I\xe2\x80\x99m so thankful that 1) the sun was shining and 2) the gardens were like a dream world. I much prefer a slower pace of life so visiting these areas and seeking places of tranquillity is so important! It was my first staycation in a while and has made me realise once again everything that England has to offer, beautiful gardens being one of them! We are lucky to experience all 4 seasons so we can appreciate the changes in nature that come with them.\xe2\x80\x9d

How are you rediscovering travel this year? Tag your posts with #ExploreNextDoor and @bookingcom - we'll be re-sharing your stories and snaps."

b'Why travel to New York when you can explore the real thing next door? This summer, our UK travellers chose memories over miles, exploring the medieval city of York, just outside their doorstep. Where did you spend your summer vacation? Share your favourite close-to-home escape in the comments below. #ExploreNextDoor'

b'Dreaming of a magical getaway near home? Cardiff, Wales might be the place for you. Explore the centuries-old castles, magical beech wood forests and lush parks that will make anyone believe in fairytales.

Start your quest with a visit to Cardiff Castle, right in the heart of the city, where 2,000 years of history is waiting to be discovered. Stop by the castle rooftop for a 360-degree view of the city before exploring the grounds where you can spot the resident birds of prey. 

Hit the link in our bio to find more sights to see in the Land of Dragons. #ExploreNextDoor #wales #cardiff #welsh #greatbritain #uk #cardiffcastle #butepark #cymru'
